    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The parameterized `WITHDRAWAL_CREDENTIALS_LENGTH` was for making it clearer in the length checks. But @daejunpark is considering removing the length checks later (see the discussion from this thread: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1362/files#r320008295).\r\n\r\nI personally think `bytes32` is a common alias in Vyper contracts. After the length checks are removed, we could either keep parameters:\r\n```python\r\ndef deposit(pubkey: bytes[PUBKEY_LENGTH],\r\n            withdrawal_credentials: bytes[HASH_LENGTH],\r\n            signature: bytes[SIGNATURE_LENGTH],\r\n            deposit_data_root: bytes[HASH_LENGTH]):\r\n```\r\nor just\r\n```python\r\ndef deposit(pubkey: bytes[48],\r\n            withdrawal_credentials: bytes32,\r\n            signature: bytes[96],\r\n            deposit_data_root: bytes32):\r\n```",
